Open terminal in local laptop:
STEP 1: Generate ssh key in local terminal
command: ssh-keygen
press enter,then yes, now key is generate

check if key is generated:
ls ~/.ssh
we can see 2 keys( ex: id_ed2551, id_ed2551.pub OR id_rsa, id_rsa.pub)

now we need to copy the content of pub file and paste it on the aws ec2 
command: cat ~/.ssh/id_ed2551.pub
need to copy that nd paste on aws ec2
first run this command on ec2:

mkdir ~/.ssh
nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

then paste that key

then Ctrl + O
then enter
then Ctrl + X

See if the key got saved: cat ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
you can see the key, that means that remote server is now allowed to login to the ec2

